nodes.text: Dee Skaak was a Human female member of the Skaak Tippers who lived during the Galactic Civil War.

Following the Battle of Yavin, Dee Skaak had become a leader of the Skaak Tippers, a criminal group of slicers and information brokers active on Naboo. Dee Skaak operated from a cave in the Gallo Mountains. Circa 1 ABY, Tomi Skaak's group had stolen a valuable Gungan artifact and transferred it to Dee Skaak. Boss Rugor Nass then sent a spacer to the Skaak Tipper Bunker in order to retrieve the Gungan artifact. Several Skaak Tippers, including Tomi Skaak were killed during the assault. The spacer later went to the Skaak Tipper Cave and killed Dee Skaak to finally recover the artifact.

Dee Skaak was a non-player character in the 2003 video game Star Wars Galaxies, a massively multiplayer online role-playing game developed by Sony Online Entertainment and published by LucasArts, prior to its closure on December 15, 2011. Dee Skaak was added to the game as part of the "Legacy Quest" with the release of the "Publish 25", a.k.a. the "New Game Enhancements", on November 15, 2005.
